hness, aversion and ignorance create endless dramas and fears. Beneath these is a quiet stillness where you can get to know yourself; this is a wondrous and beautiful experience. Whether you practice for just ten minutes a day or longer does not matter. You are releasing your limitations, while opening to self-acceptance and awareness.\r\n\r\n<strong>5. Awakening Forgiveness</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.care2.com/greenliving/if-you-cant-forgive-you-cant-dance.html\" target=\"_blank\">Forgiveness</a> is the greatest gift you can give yourself and others. As you sit in meditation and watch your thoughts and feelings moving through you, so you can observe that who you are now is not who you were just a moment ago, let alone a day, a week, or a month ago. Who you, or someone else, was when pain was caused is not who you are now. When you experience your essential interconnectedness you see how the ignorance of this creates separation and suffering, so that forgiveness for such ignorance arises spontaneously.\r\n\r\n<strong>6. Generating Harmlessness</strong>\r\n\r\nSimply through the intent to cause less pain you can bring greater dignity to your world, so that harm is replaced with harmlessness and disrespect with respect. Harm is usually caused unintentionally, whether by ignoring someone’s feelings, putting yourself down, reaffirming your hopelessness, disliking your appearance, or seeing yourself as incompetent or unworthy. How much resentment, guilt, or shame are you holding on to, thus perpetuating harmfulness? Meditation enables you transform this through recognizing your essential goodness and the preciousness of all life.\r\n\r\n<strong>7. Appreciating Appreciation</strong>\r\n\r\nTake a moment to appreciate the chair you are sitting on. Consider how the chair was made: the wood, cotton, wool, or other fibers, the trees and plants that were used, the earth that grew the trees, the sun and rain, the animals that maybe gave their lives, the people who prepared the materials, the factory where the chair was made, the designer and carpenter and seamstress, the shop that sold it—all this just so you could be sitting here, now. Then extend that deep <a href=\"http://www.care2.com/greenliving/practice-true-gratitude.html\" target=\"_blank\">appreciation</a> to everything and everyone in your life.\r\n\r\n<strong>8. Being Aware</strong>\r\n\r\nAwareness is the key to awakening. Through awareness you can see your monkey mind and all its mischief. Almost everything we do is to achieve something: if we do this, then we will get that; if we do that, then this will happen. But in meditation you do it just to do it. There is no ulterior purpose other than to be here, in the present moment, without trying to get anywhere or achieve anything. You are just aware of whatever is happening, whether pleasant or unpleasant. No judgment, no right or wrong. Simply being aware. Enjoy!', '8 Ways Meditation Can Change Your Life', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '39-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-11-15 14:16:29', '2015-11-15 14:16:29', '', '39', 'http://localhost/sharingMT/index.php/2015/11/15/39-autosave-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('43', '1', '2015-11-15 14:21:15', '2015-11-15 14:21:15', '<div>From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>\r\n<div dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\">\r\n<div>\"NGO\" redirects here. For other uses, see <a title=\"NGO (disambiguation)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NGO_%28disambiguation%29\">NGO (disambiguation)</a>.</div>\r\n</div>\r\nA <strong>non-governmental organization</strong> (<strong>NGO</strong>) is an <a title=\"Organization\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Organization\">organization</a> that is neither a part of a <a title=\"Government\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government\">government</a> nor a conventional for-profit <a title=\"Business\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Business\">business</a>.\r\n\r\nUsually set up by ordinary citizens, NGOs may be funded by governments, foundations, businesses, or private persons. Some avoid formal funding altogether and are run primarily by volunteers. NGOs are highly diverse groups of organizations engaged in a wide range of activities, and take different forms in different parts of the world. Some may have charitable status, while others may be registered for tax exemption based on recognition of social purposes. Others may be fronts for political, religious, or other interests.\r\n\r\nThe number of NGOs in the <a title=\"United States\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States\">United States</a> is estimated at 1.5 million.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-1\">[1]</a></sup> <a title=\"Russia\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russia\">Russia</a> has 277,000 NGOs.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-2\">[2]</a></sup> <a title=\"India\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India\">India</a> is estimated to have had around 2 million NGOs in 2009, just over one NGO per 600 Indians, and many times the number of primary schools and primary health centres in India.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-3\">[3]</a></sup><sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-4\">[4]</a></sup>\r\n\r\nNGOs are difficult to define, and the term \'NGO\' is not always used consistently. In some countries the term NGO is applied to an organization that in another country would be called an <a title=\"Nonprofit organization\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nonprofit_organization\">NPO</a> (nonprofit organization), and vice-versa. There are many different classifications of NGO in use. The most common focus is on \"orientation\" and \"level of operation\". An NGO\'s orientation refers to the type of activities it takes on. These activities might include human rights, environmental, improving health, or development work. An NGO\'s level of operation indicates the scale at which an organization works, such as local, regional, national, or international.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-5\">[5]</a></sup>\r\n\r\nThe term \"non-governmental organization\" was first coined in 1945, when the United Nations (UN) was created.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-6\">[6]</a></sup> The UN, itself an <a title=\"Inter-governmental organization\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inter-governmental_organization\">inter-governmental organization</a>, made it possible for certain approved specialized international non-state agencies — <em>i.e.</em>, non-governmental organizations — to be awarded observer status at its assemblies and some of its meetings. Later the term became used more widely. Today, according to the UN, any kind of private organization that is independent from government control can be termed an \"NGO\", provided it is not-for-profit, nonprevention, and not simply an opposition political party.\r\n\r\nOne characteristic these diverse organizations share is that their non-profit status means they are not hindered by short-term financial objectives. Accordingly, they are able to devote themselves to issues which occur across longer time horizons, such as climate change, malaria prevention or a global ban on landmines. Public surveys reveal that NGOs often enjoy a high degree of public trust, which can make them a useful – but not always sufficient – proxy for the concerns of society and stakeholders.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-7\">[7]</a></sup>', 'Non-governmental organization', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'non-governmental-organization', '', '', '2015-11-15 14:22:24', '2015-11-15 14:22:24', '', '0', 'http://localhost/sharingMT/?p=43', '0', 'post', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('44', '1', '2015-11-15 14:20:55', '2015-11-15 14:20:55', '', 'businessman-pointing-ngo-non-governmental-organization-sign-virtual-screen-people-icons-linked-as-network-49726411', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', 'businessman-pointing-ngo-non-governmental-organization-sign-virtual-screen-people-icons-linked-as-network-49726411', '', '', '2015-11-15 14:20:55', '2015-11-15 14:20:55', '', '43', 'http://localhost/sharingMT/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/businessman-pointing-ngo-non-governmental-organization-sign-virtual-screen-people-icons-linked-as-network-49726411.jpg', '0', 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('45', '1', '2015-11-15 14:21:15', '2015-11-15 14:21:15', '<div><a href=\"http://localhost/sharingMT/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/businessman-pointing-ngo-non-governmental-organization-sign-virtual-screen-people-icons-linked-as-network-49726411.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-44\" src=\"http://localhost/sharingMT/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/businessman-pointing-ngo-non-governmental-organization-sign-virtual-screen-people-icons-linked-as-network-49726411-300x220.jpg\" alt=\"businessman-pointing-ngo-non-governmental-organization-sign-virtual-screen-people-icons-linked-as-network-49726411\" width=\"300\" height=\"220\" /></a>From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>\r\n<div dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\">\r\n<div>\"NGO\" redirects here. For other uses, see <a title=\"NGO (disambiguation)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NGO_%28disambiguation%29\">NGO (disambiguation)</a>.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Ministru_prezidents_Valdis_Dombrovskis_tiekas_ar_Nevalstisko_organiz%C4%81ciju_un_Ministru_kabineta_sadarb%C4%ABbas_memorandu_parakst%C4%ABju%C5%A1%C4%81m_nevalstiskaj%C4%81m_organiz%C4%81cij%C4%81m_%288435701674%29.jpg\"><img src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/58/Ministru_prezidents_Valdis_Dombrovskis_tiekas_ar_Nevalstisko_organiz%C4%81ciju_un_Ministru_kabineta_sadarb%C4%ABbas_memorandu_parakst%C4%ABju%C5%A1%C4%81m_nevalstiskaj%C4%81m_organiz%C4%81cij%C4%81m_%288435701674%29.jpg/220px-thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"220\" height=\"147\" data-file-width=\"3000\" data-file-height=\"2000\" /></a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><a title=\"Valdis Dombrovskis\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Valdis_Dombrovskis\">Valdis Dombrovskis</a>, then <a title=\"Prime Minister of Latvia\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Latvia\">Prime Minister of Latvia</a>, meeting an NGO representative</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\nA <strong>non-governmental organization</strong> (<strong>NGO</strong>) is an <a title=\"Organization\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Organization\">organization</a> that is neither a part of a <a title=\"Government\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government\">government</a> nor a conventional for-profit <a title=\"Business\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Business\">business</a>.\r\n\r\nUsually set up by ordinary citizens, NGOs may be funded by governments, foundations, businesses, or private persons. Some avoid formal funding altogether and are run primarily by volunteers. NGOs are highly diverse groups of organizations engaged in a wide range of activities, and take different forms in different parts of the world. Some may have charitable status, while others may be registered for tax exemption based on recognition of social purposes. Others may be fronts for political, religious, or other interests.\r\n\r\nThe number of NGOs in the <a title=\"United States\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States\">United States</a> is estimated at 1.5 million.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-1\">[1]</a></sup> <a title=\"Russia\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russia\">Russia</a> has 277,000 NGOs.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-2\">[2]</a></sup> <a title=\"India\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India\">India</a> is estimated to have had around 2 million NGOs in 2009, just over one NGO per 600 Indians, and many times the number of primary schools and primary health centres in India.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-3\">[3]</a></sup><sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-4\">[4]</a></sup>\r\n\r\nNGOs are difficult to define, and the term \'NGO\' is not always used consistently. In some countries the term NGO is applied to an organization that in another country would be called an <a title=\"Nonprofit organization\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nonprofit_organization\">NPO</a> (nonprofit organization), and vice-versa. There are many different classifications of NGO in use. The most common focus is on \"orientation\" and \"level of operation\". An NGO\'s orientation refers to the type of activities it takes on. These activities might include human rights, environmental, improving health, or development work. An NGO\'s level of operation indicates the scale at which an organization works, such as local, regional, national, or international.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-5\">[5]</a></sup>\r\n\r\nThe term \"non-governmental organization\" was first coined in 1945, when the United Nations (UN) was created.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-6\">[6]</a></sup> The UN, itself an <a title=\"Inter-governmental organization\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inter-governmental_organization\">inter-governmental organization</a>, made it possible for certain approved specialized international non-state agencies — <em>i.e.</em>, non-governmental organizations — to be awarded observer status at its assemblies and some of its meetings. Later the term became used more widely. Today, according to the UN, any kind of private organization that is independent from government control can be termed an \"NGO\", provided it is not-for-profit, nonprevention, and not simply an opposition political party.\r\n\r\nOne characteristic these diverse organizations share is that their non-profit status means they are not hindered by short-term financial objectives. Accordingly, they are able to devote themselves to issues which occur across longer time horizons, such as climate change, malaria prevention or a global ban on landmines. Public surveys reveal that NGOs often enjoy a high degree of public trust, which can make them a useful – but not always sufficient – proxy for the concerns of society and stakeholders.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-7\">[7]</a></sup>', 'Non-governmental organization', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '43-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-11-15 14:21:15', '2015-11-15 14:21:15', '', '43', 'http://localhost/sharingMT/index.php/2015/11/15/43-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('46', '1', '2015-11-15 14:21:22', '2015-11-15 14:21:22', '<div><a href=\"http://localhost/sharingMT/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/businessman-pointing-ngo-non-governmental-organization-sign-virtual-screen-people-icons-linked-as-network-49726411.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-44\" src=\"http://localhost/sharingMT/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/businessman-pointing-ngo-non-governmental-organization-sign-virtual-screen-people-icons-linked-as-network-49726411-300x220.jpg\" alt=\"businessman-pointing-ngo-non-governmental-organization-sign-virtual-screen-people-icons-linked-as-network-49726411\" width=\"300\" height=\"220\" /></a>From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>\r\n<div dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\">\r\n<div>\"NGO\" redirects here. For other uses, see <a title=\"NGO (disambiguation)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NGO_%28disambiguation%29\">NGO (disambiguation)</a>.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Ministru_prezidents_Valdis_Dombrovskis_tiekas_ar_Nevalstisko_organiz%C4%81ciju_un_Ministru_kabineta_sadarb%C4%ABbas_memorandu_parakst%C4%ABju%C5%A1%C4%81m_nevalstiskaj%C4%81m_organiz%C4%81cij%C4%81m_%288435701674%29.jpg\"><img src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/58/Ministru_prezidents_Valdis_Dombrovskis_tiekas_ar_Nevalstisko_organiz%C4%81ciju_un_Ministru_kabineta_sadarb%C4%ABbas_memorandu_parakst%C4%ABju%C5%A1%C4%81m_nevalstiskaj%C4%81m_organiz%C4%81cij%C4%81m_%288435701674%29.jpg/220px-thumbnail.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"220\" height=\"147\" data-file-width=\"3000\" data-file-height=\"2000\" /></a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><a title=\"Valdis Dombrovskis\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Valdis_Dombrovskis\">Valdis Dombrovskis</a>, then <a title=\"Prime Minister of Latvia\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Latvia\">Prime Minister of Latvia</a>, meeting an NGO representative</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\nA <strong>non-governmental organization</strong> (<strong>NGO</strong>) is an <a title=\"Organization\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Organization\">organization</a> that is neither a part of a <a title=\"Government\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government\">government</a> nor a conventional for-profit <a title=\"Business\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Business\">business</a>.\r\n\r\nUsually set up by ordinary citizens, NGOs may be funded by governments, foundations, businesses, or private persons. Some avoid formal funding altogether and are run primarily by volunteers. NGOs are highly diverse groups of organizations engaged in a wide range of activities, and take different forms in different parts of the world. Some may have charitable status, while others may be registered for tax exemption based on recognition of social purposes. Others may be fronts for political, religious, or other interests.\r\n\r\nThe number of NGOs in the <a title=\"United States\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States\">United States</a> is estimated at 1.5 million.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-1\">[1]</a></sup> <a title=\"Russia\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russia\">Russia</a> has 277,000 NGOs.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-2\">[2]</a></sup> <a title=\"India\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India\">India</a> is estimated to have had around 2 million NGOs in 2009, just over one NGO per 600 Indians, and many times the number of primary schools and primary health centres in India.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-3\">[3]</a></sup><sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-4\">[4]</a></sup>\r\n\r\nNGOs are difficult to define, and the term \'NGO\' is not always used consistently. In some countries the term NGO is applied to an organization that in another country would be called an <a title=\"Nonprofit organization\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nonprofit_organization\">NPO</a> (nonprofit organization), and vice-versa. There are many different classifications of NGO in use. The most common focus is on \"orientation\" and \"level of operation\". An NGO\'s orientation refers to the type of activities it takes on. These activities might include human rights, environmental, improving health, or development work. An NGO\'s level of operation indicates the scale at which an organization works, such as local, regional, national, or international.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-5\">[5]</a></sup>\r\n\r\nThe term \"non-governmental organization\" was first coined in 1945, when the United Nations (UN) was created.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-6\">[6]</a></sup> The UN, itself an <a title=\"Inter-governmental organization\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inter-governmental_organization\">inter-governmental organization</a>, made it possible for certain approved specialized international non-state agencies — <em>i.e.</em>, non-governmental organizations — to be awarded observer status at its assemblies and some of its meetings. Later the term became used more widely. Today, according to the UN, any kind of private organization that is independent from government control can be termed an \"NGO\", provided it is not-for-profit, nonprevention, and not simply an opposition political party.\r\n\r\nOne characteristic these diverse organizations share is that their non-profit status means they are not hindered by short-term financial objectives. Accordingly, they are able to devote themselves to issues which occur across longer time horizons, such as climate change, malaria prevention or a global ban on landmines. Public surveys reveal that NGOs often enjoy a high degree of public trust, which can make them a useful – but not always sufficient – proxy for the concerns of society and stakeholders.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-7\">[7]</a></sup>', 'Non-governmental organization', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '43-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-11-15 14:21:22', '2015-11-15 14:21:22', '', '43', 'http://localhost/sharingMT/index.php/2015/11/15/43-autosave-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('47', '1', '2015-11-15 14:21:36', '2015-11-15 14:21:36', '<div><a href=\"http://localhost/sharingMT/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/businessman-pointing-ngo-non-governmental-organization-sign-virtual-screen-people-icons-linked-as-network-49726411.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-44\" src=\"http://localhost/sharingMT/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/businessman-pointing-ngo-non-governmental-organization-sign-virtual-screen-people-icons-linked-as-network-49726411-300x220.jpg\" alt=\"businessman-pointing-ngo-non-governmental-organization-sign-virtual-screen-people-icons-linked-as-network-49726411\" width=\"300\" height=\"220\" /></a>From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>\r\n<div dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\">\r\n<div>\"NGO\" redirects here. For other uses, see <a title=\"NGO (disambiguation)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NGO_%28disambiguation%29\">NGO (disambiguation)</a>.</div>\r\n<div></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><a title=\"Valdis Dombrovskis\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Valdis_Dombrovskis\">Valdis Dombrovskis</a>, then <a title=\"Prime Minister of Latvia\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_Minister_of_Latvia\">Prime Minister of Latvia</a>, meeting an NGO representative</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\nA <strong>non-governmental organization</strong> (<strong>NGO</strong>) is an <a title=\"Organization\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Organization\">organization</a> that is neither a part of a <a title=\"Government\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government\">government</a> nor a conventional for-profit <a title=\"Business\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Business\">business</a>.\r\n\r\nUsually set up by ordinary citizens, NGOs may be funded by governments, foundations, businesses, or private persons. Some avoid formal funding altogether and are run primarily by volunteers. NGOs are highly diverse groups of organizations engaged in a wide range of activities, and take different forms in different parts of the world. Some may have charitable status, while others may be registered for tax exemption based on recognition of social purposes. Others may be fronts for political, religious, or other interests.\r\n\r\nThe number of NGOs in the <a title=\"United States\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States\">United States</a> is estimated at 1.5 million.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-1\">[1]</a></sup> <a title=\"Russia\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russia\">Russia</a> has 277,000 NGOs.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-2\">[2]</a></sup> <a title=\"India\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India\">India</a> is estimated to have had around 2 million NGOs in 2009, just over one NGO per 600 Indians, and many times the number of primary schools and primary health centres in India.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-3\">[3]</a></sup><sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-4\">[4]</a></sup>\r\n\r\nNGOs are difficult to define, and the term \'NGO\' is not always used consistently. In some countries the term NGO is applied to an organization that in another country would be called an <a title=\"Nonprofit organization\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nonprofit_organization\">NPO</a> (nonprofit organization), and vice-versa. There are many different classifications of NGO in use. The most common focus is on \"orientation\" and \"level of operation\". An NGO\'s orientation refers to the type of activities it takes on. These activities might include human rights, environmental, improving health, or development work. An NGO\'s level of operation indicates the scale at which an organization works, such as local, regional, national, or international.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-5\">[5]</a></sup>\r\n\r\nThe term \"non-governmental organization\" was first coined in 1945, when the United Nations (UN) was created.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-6\">[6]</a></sup> The UN, itself an <a title=\"Inter-governmental organization\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inter-governmental_organization\">inter-governmental organization</a>, made it possible for certain approved specialized international non-state agencies — <em>i.e.</em>, non-governmental organizations — to be awarded observer status at its assemblies and some of its meetings. Later the term became used more widely. Today, according to the UN, any kind of private organization that is independent from government control can be termed an \"NGO\", provided it is not-for-profit, nonprevention, and not simply an opposition political party.\r\n\r\nOne characteristic these diverse organizations share is that their non-profit status means they are not hindered by short-term financial objectives. Accordingly, they are able to devote themselves to issues which occur across longer time horizons, such as climate change, malaria prevention or a global ban on landmines. Public surveys reveal that NGOs often enjoy a high degree of public trust, which can make them a useful – but not always sufficient – proxy for the concerns of society and stakeholders.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-7\">[7]</a></sup>', 'Non-governmental organization', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '43-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-11-15 14:21:36', '2015-11-15 14:21:36', '', '43', 'http://localhost/sharingMT/index.php/2015/11/15/43-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('48', '1', '2015-11-15 14:22:24', '2015-11-15 14:22:24', '<div>From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>\r\n<div dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\">\r\n<div>\"NGO\" redirects here. For other uses, see <a title=\"NGO (disambiguation)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NGO_%28disambiguation%29\">NGO (disambiguation)</a>.</div>\r\n</div>\r\nA <strong>non-governmental organization</strong> (<strong>NGO</strong>) is an <a title=\"Organization\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Organization\">organization</a> that is neither a part of a <a title=\"Government\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government\">government</a> nor a conventional for-profit <a title=\"Business\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Business\">business</a>.\r\n\r\nUsually set up by ordinary citizens, NGOs may be funded by governments, foundations, businesses, or private persons. Some avoid formal funding altogether and are run primarily by volunteers. NGOs are highly diverse groups of organizations engaged in a wide range of activities, and take different forms in different parts of the world. Some may have charitable status, while others may be registered for tax exemption based on recognition of social purposes. Others may be fronts for political, religious, or other interests.\r\n\r\nThe number of NGOs in the <a title=\"United States\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States\">United States</a> is estimated at 1.5 million.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-1\">[1]</a></sup> <a title=\"Russia\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russia\">Russia</a> has 277,000 NGOs.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-2\">[2]</a></sup> <a title=\"India\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India\">India</a> is estimated to have had around 2 million NGOs in 2009, just over one NGO per 600 Indians, and many times the number of primary schools and primary health centres in India.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-3\">[3]</a></sup><sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-4\">[4]</a></sup>\r\n\r\nNGOs are difficult to define, and the term \'NGO\' is not always used consistently. In some countries the term NGO is applied to an organization that in another country would be called an <a title=\"Nonprofit organization\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nonprofit_organization\">NPO</a> (nonprofit organization), and vice-versa. There are many different classifications of NGO in use. The most common focus is on \"orientation\" and \"level of operation\". An NGO\'s orientation refers to the type of activities it takes on. These activities might include human rights, environmental, improving health, or development work. An NGO\'s level of operation indicates the scale at which an organization works, such as local, regional, national, or international.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-5\">[5]</a></sup>\r\n\r\nThe term \"non-governmental organization\" was first coined in 1945, when the United Nations (UN) was created.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-6\">[6]</a></sup> The UN, itself an <a title=\"Inter-governmental organization\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inter-governmental_organization\">inter-governmental organization</a>, made it possible for certain approved specialized international non-state agencies — <em>i.e.</em>, non-governmental organizations — to be awarded observer status at its assemblies and some of its meetings. Later the term became used more widely. Today, according to the UN, any kind of private organization that is independent from government control can be termed an \"NGO\", provided it is not-for-profit, nonprevention, and not simply an opposition political party.\r\n\r\nOne characteristic these diverse organizations share is that their non-profit status means they are not hindered by short-term financial objectives. Accordingly, they are able to devote themselves to issues which occur across longer time horizons, such as climate change, malaria prevention or a global ban on landmines. Public surveys reveal that NGOs often enjoy a high degree of public trust, which can make them a useful – but not always sufficient – proxy for the concerns of society and stakeholders.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-governmental_organization#cite_note-7\">[7]</a></sup>', 'Non-governmental organization', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '43-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-11-15 14:22:24', '2015-11-15 14:22:24', '', '43', 'http://localhost/sharingMT/index.php/2015/11/15/43-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES ('49', '1', '2015-11-15 14:29:47', '2015-11-15 14:29:47', '<a href=\"http://localhost/sharingMT/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/meditation-ky-anh-agawood-3.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-50\" src=\"http://localhost/sharingMT/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/meditation-ky-anh-agawood-3-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"meditation-ky-anh-agawood-3\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" /></a>Thiền định có suy ý nghĩa rất lớn, và hay mà có thể bạn chưa biết. Đôi khi cách tìm lại chính mình là khi buông thả mọi thứ ...\r\n\r\nSuy nghĩ nhiều, xác định mục tiêu, theo sau mục tiêu, nỗ lực hết mình,.. nghe có vẻ đối lập với thiền định . Thiền định theo cá nhân mình nghĩ là, khi tâm thả lỏng, không còn nghĩ ngợi. Trong đầu không còn tham vọng, ham muốn, mục tiêu... Nói chung , chẳng ngờ được sự thả lỏng mình đó, lại làm cho bạn trở nên có khả năng hơn..\r\n\r\nThiền định là về sống châm. Có đôi khi, bạn cảm thấy mình đang sống nhanh quá ?\r\n\r\nHãy cùng tìm hiểu về thiền định.!', 'cảm nhận riêng về thiền định', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'cam-nhan-rieng-ve-thien-dinh', '', '', '2015-11-15 14:32:28', '2015-11-15 14:32:28', '', '0', 'http://localhost/sharingMT/?p=49', '0', 'post', '', '0');
